[src:logistic-regression/maximum-likelihood-estimation] Gradient descent method requires to calculate the gradient at the *r*-th iteration, but no need to calculate the inverse of second-order derivative, i.e., the Hessian matrix.
[src:logistic-regression/maximum-likelihood-estimation] Therefore, it is computationally faster than Newton–Raphson method.
